# =============================================================================
#  Line ending policy for the repo.
#
#  `* text=auto eol=lf` says: detect text files automatically, and whenever
#  git stores or checks one out, use LF (\n) line endings regardless of OS.
#  This stops Windows editors from silently flipping files to CRLF and
#  creating diffs that look like every line changed.
#
#  Binary files are matched explicitly so they're never touched.
#
#  After editing this file, run `git add --renormalize .` once to bring the
#  existing working tree in line with the new rule. One-time cost.
# =============================================================================

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binaries — never normalize, never diff as text.
*.png    binary
*.jpg    binary
*.jpeg   binary
*.gif    binary
*.ico    binary
*.pdf    binary
*.woff   binary
*.woff2  binary
*.ttf    binary
*.otf    binary
*.eot    binary
*.mp3    binary
*.mp4    binary
*.webp   binary
*.zip    binary
